      • get

        public <TObject extends ArtObject> ArtObjectMeta<TObject> get()
        Description copied from interface: ArtObjectMeta
        Tries to cast this ArtObjectMeta into the target type. You should only use this method if you are sure that the ArtObjectMeta.artObjectClass() matches the required target class. If that is not the case, null will be returned.

        This is useful if you have collections of 

        ArtObjectInformation
        and want to pass individual types of the object to other methods like ActionProvider.add(ArtObjectMeta). Make sure you do a 
        YourTargetArtObject.class.isAssignableFrom(this.getArtObjectClass)
        check before using this method. Otherwise null is very likely.
        Specified by:
        get in interface ArtObjectMeta<TArtObject extends ArtObject>
        Type Parameters:
        TObject - type of the ArtObject you need
        Returns:
        this ArtObjectMeta with the concrete ArtObject type

      • initialize

        public ArtObjectMeta<TArtObject> initialize()
                                     throws ArtMetaDataException
        Description copied from interface: ArtObjectMeta
        Initializes the Factory, loads all annotations and checks if the ArtObject is configured correctly.

        If everything looks good the ArtObject is registered for execution. If not a ArtMetaDataException is thrown.

        Specified by:
        initialize in interface ArtObjectMeta<TArtObject extends ArtObject>
        Throws:
        ArtMetaDataException - if the ArtObject could not be registered.
